<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Dwarven foresigh<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.64)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=13107'>Ricardo "Nsammael" Nieto</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=13107&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 6, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> <br />
<br />
Hi guys, this is my second article, and i´ll talk about Dwarves. I hope you enjoy with the read.<br />
<br />
FIrst of all, th companions. Gimli is the best of all. He has several version. I review all that:<br />
<br />
FotR set:<br />
<br />
   -->Gimli, Dwarf of Erebor  TC:2<br />
      ST:6  VT:3  SG:Aragorn<br />
      Damage +1. <br />
      Fellowship: If the TP has fewer than 2, add 2 to place a card from hand beneath your draw deck.<br />
<br />
At first time, this Gimli sucks. Why do you want to pay to place a card at the end of the deck? But, if you see the FotR spoiler, you can see a Moria condition, that let you to take an orc from bottom of deck, UNDERDEEPS OF MORIA. Hohoho, place together, with other cards that let you place orcs in bottom, like GOBLIN SNEAK and make a late swarm. This is the basics of Moria deeps deck.<br />
<br />
   -->Gimli, Son of Gloin   TC:2<br />
      ST:6  VT:3  SG:Gandalf<br />
      Damage +1. <br />
      Skirmish: Exert Gimli to make him strengh +2<br />
<br />
Well, this was the best skirmisher until Eomer appears in TTT set. He is a beast. With axes, DWARVEN BRACERS and ENDURANCE OF DWARVES, he can kill each minion in the game. In addition, he is Gandalf signet, that is great for TRUST ME ONCE YOU DID decks.<br />
 <br />
<br />
MoM set:<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli, dwarf of the mountain race   TC:2<br />
       ST:6  VT:3  SG:Frodo<br />
       Damage +1. <br />
       Each underground site&#8217;s Shadow number is &#8211;2.<br />
<br />
This is, in my opinion, the worst Gimli ever printed. In FotR block, he has some utility, because you must go through one underground site, at least, but, in TTT, only two sites are undergrounds, and it may be you never see an underground. In RotK is worst. 0 underground sites make him useless. I don´t see play anytime.<br />
<br />
<br />
TTT set:<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli, lockbearer   TC:2<br />
       ST:6  VT:3  SG:Aragorn<br />
       Damage +1. <br />
       Gimli is strengh +1 for each unbound hobbit you can spot.<br />
<br />
With this guy, you have a 8 strengh for 2 twilight. You can start with this and the 3 hobbits, or, more usual, start with the hobbits, LEGOLAS, DAUNTLESS HUNTER, and play this, if you don´t want use ARAGORN, WINFOOT, or ARAGORN, KING IN EXILE. I make a deck, (If you want review that, see http://decktech.net/lotr/decks/decks.php?deck=31157) that use hime us main fighter.<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli, unbidden guest   TC:2<br />
       ST:6  VT:3  SG:Gandalf<br />
       Damage +1. <br />
       Skirmish: Exert Gimli to make an unbound companion strength +1 (or +2 if that companion is Legolas).<br />
<br />
Another great Gimli. He is close to GIMLI, SON OF GLOIN, but you can pump other guy, not only him. And, if you have Legolas, he is money. This card, with LEGOLAS, ELVEN COMRADE are the core of the cheapest version (not worse, only cheaper) of TRUST ME ONCE YOU DID decks.<br />
<br />
<br />
BoHD set:<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli, Skilled defender  TC:2<br />
       ST:6  VT:3  SG:Theoden<br />
       Damage +1. <br />
       Each time Gimli wins a skirmish, you may wound a minion assigned to skirmish an unbound companion.<br />
<br />
<br />
This Gimli is your choice in a Elf/Dwarf deck. With some archery, and events like LEND US YOUR AID, combined with LEGOLAS, ARCHER OF MIRKWOOD, you can kill several minions with one companion. But, you must be careful, becouse he don´t pump himself, as GIMLI, SON OF GLOIN can. Keep events in hand to win the skirmish. And you must have attention with Frodo assignement, because you can wound the minion he was skirmishing.<br />
<br />
<br />
RotK set:<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli, faithful companion  TC:2<br />
       ST:6  VT:3  SG:Theoden<br />
       Damage +1. <br />
       While you have initiative, Gimli is strengh +2<br />
<br />
Great Gimli. You can start with two companions, and one of them of 8 strengh. Only EOMER, SKILLED TACTICIAN, have this stats. You may use this Gimli with a deck that draw 4 cards per turn. Pure dwarf can. With DELVING and CALCULATED RISK you draw 3 cards. Other interested cards are EVER MY HEART RISES, SEARCH FAR AND WIDE or OUT OF DARKNESS. All this cards will let you fight with a 8 ST companion almost every time.<br />
<br />
     -->Gimli, Feared axeman    TC:2<br />
        ST:6  VT:3  SG:Aragorn<br />
        Damage +1. <br />
        Response: If a [dwarf] condition is about to be discarded by an opponent, exert a dwarf o discard a [dwarf] card from hand to prevent this.<br />
<br />
Lol. This Gimli make stacking strategy viable. The protection this Gimli give, is unpayable. You can protect that EVER MY HEART RISE with 3 important cards, or the two ENDURANCE OF DWARVES, that they avoid to Gimli will slaughtered. Great Gimli.<br />
<br />
<br />
Other companions:<br />
<br />
     -->Farin, dwarven emissary  TC:2<br />
        ST:5  VT:3 <br />
        To play, spot a dwarf<br />
        While skirmishing an orc, Farin is strengh +2<br />
<br />
The first partner of Gimli, Farin is great against several cultures, Moria, Isengard orcs (and wargs), Sauron and the new ringwraiths orc.<br />
<br />
<br />
     -->Fror, Gimli´s kinsman  TC:2<br />
        ST:5  VT:3 <br />
        To play, spot a dwarf<br />
        While skirmishing an uruk-hai, Fror is strengh +3<br />
<br />
Similar to Farin, Fror is great against one of the most played cultures in game. Uruk-hais. With an axe (or two), he can win any skirmish against that ugly race.<br />
<br />
     -->Gloin, Friend to Thorin  TC:2<br />
        ST:5  VT:3 <br />
        For each [dwarf] tale you can spot, Gloin is strengh +1 (limit +4)<br />
<br />
Gimli´s daddy, after a few sites he became a beast. Without weapons, he used to be 8 ST or 9 ST. With axe, he can be 11 o 12 easily. The absence of damage bonus is compensated with cards, like LORD OF MORIA, or better, HERE IS A GOOD ROCK, that it give us the chance of damage +X and is a tale for GLOIN. <br />
<br />
      -->Dwarven guard   TC:1<br />
         ST:4  VT:2<br />
         To play, spot a dwarf<br />
<br />
Jejejeje, the chump-blocking guy. It´s very bad, unless you use to play DISQUIET OF OUR PEOPLE on him and block Balrog and Cave Troll. You shouldn´t play them.<br />
<br />
<br />
Dwarves has two allies. They are:<br />
<br />
   -->Grimir, Dwarven Elder  TC:1<br />
      Ally - Home 3<br />
      ST:3 VT:3<br />
      Fellowship: Exert Grimir to shuffle a [dwarf] event from your discard pile into your draw deck.<br />
<br />
This dwarf let you recuperate a pair of events. You should shuffle events of drawing cards. Despite of this, it´s not essencial to a dwarf deck.<br />
<br />
   -->Thrarin, Dwarven Smith  TC:1<br />
      Ally - Home 3<br />
      ST:4 VT:2<br />
      Maneuver: Exert Thrarin to allow him to participate in archery fire and skirmishes until the regroup phase.<br />
<br />
This is one of the best allies in the game, until GRIMA, CHIEF COUNSELOR appear. He is a permanent stealth, that he don´t clog your hand. At the beggining, i play him in EVERY deck i made. But, since BoHD release, i can´t use him, except in a dwarf deck or dwarf/X deck.<br />
<br />
<br />
After the companions, the weapons. They get several hand weapon (axes, of course):<br />
<br />
    -->Gimli´s battle   TC:2<br />
       ST: +2<br />
       Bearer must be Gimli. <br />
       He is damage +1. Each time Gimli wins a skirmish, you may wound an Orc.<br />
<br />
FotR. Great weapon. Gimli receive a permanent +2, and damage +1. In addition, he gain the ability of wound an orc. Money against Moria.<br />
<br />
    -->Dwarven axe   TC:0<br />
       Bearer must be a dwarf<br />
       ST: +2<br />
       Each time a player&#8217;s minion loses a skirmish to<br />
bearer, that player discards the top card from his draw deck.<br />
<br />
FotR. The cheapest free people weapon in the game. They can be put in ANY dwarf, companion or ally. He helps in a dwarf discard deck, but, that kind of deck has never been played.<br />
But, a must in a dwarf deck.<br />
<br />
     -->Hand axe   TC:0<br />
       Bearer must be a Dwarf. <br />
       ST: +1<br />
       This weapon may be borne in addition to 1 other hand weapon. <br />
       Archery: Discard this weapon to make the fellowship archery total +1.<br />
<br />
MoM. Dwarf decks needs some archery wounds. This weapons allows us to shot some undirected archery. It´s twilight cost allows to play them without some kind of problem too.<br />
<br />
     -->Axe of Erebor  TC:2<br />
        Bearer must be Gimli. <br />
        ST: +2<br />
        He is damage +1. <br />
        Skirmish: Discard a [dwarf] condition or a card stacked on a [dwarf] condition to make Gimli strength +1.<br />
<br />
TTT. Alternative to GIMLI´S BATTLE AXE, this weapon is great in stacking strategy. It go well with EVEN MY HEART RISES. With the tale, you may make Gimli streght +8. With the permanent +2 and other conditions, like HERE IS A GOOD ROCK or DWARVEN HEART (great combo: heal twice and you discard it in skirmish to avoid the exerts at the beggining of turn) you may make a insanely Gimli. <br />
<br />
     -->GIMLI´S BATTLE AXE, TRUSTED WEAPON  TC:2<br />
        Bearer must be a dwarf<br />
        ST: +2<br />
        While you can spot a threat, bearer is damage +1. While you can spot 2 threats, bearer is strengh +1. While you can spot 3 threats, the fellowship archery total is +1<br />
<br />
RotK. First of all, you must realize that bearer is not limited to Gimli. This allow play this weapon and AXE OF EREBOR in Gimli. Hohoho. Two great weapons in the same deck. Great. But, how can you get the threats? Easily form is with MERRY, ROHIRRIM SQUIRE. Other forms are KNIGHT´S SPEAR (for Gondor), CALCULATED RISK or DARK WAYS (for the own dwarves), or simply, with sites. With all of them, you have a +3, damage +1 and archery +1 weapon for your dwarves.<br />
<br />
<br />
Other possesions:<br />
  <br />
To avoid this article was too long, i skip the other possesion. Maybe someday i write about them.<br />
<br />
Events and conditions:<br />
<br />
Same that above. Only two words. Dwarves make good uses from tales. Example of this are GLOIN, FRIEND TO THORIN, or MINES OF KHAZAD DUM, that let you heal your dwarves for each tale you play.<br />
Played tales are: <br />
   -->Greatest kingdom of my people: against Moria<br />
   -->Ever my heart rises: to have a new hand in support area<br />
   -->Here is a good rock: more damage<br />
   -->Stairs of Khazad Dum: against Moria, although less played than GKomP<br />
<br />
The main events of Dwarf are draw events and pump events. He has the best draw power. With card like DELVING, EVER MY HEART RISES and CALCULATED RISK.<br />
 Pumps are important for dwarfs. Best of all is FLURRY OF BLOWS (+4 and damage +1 with two weapons)<br />
<br />
<br />
Estrategies:<br />
<br />
    Dwarves has several strategy:<br />
<br />
     -->Beatdown: This estrategy is based in win all skirmish, and kill all minion with de damage bonus of certain cards. You should have some drawing events and many pumpers. This make this deck big. Paired with Moria is the best option. A sample deck of this would be as the following:<br />
<br />
Frodo <br />
Ring<br />
<br />
Companions  (6 cards)<br />
<br />
Gimli, Son of Gloin (Starting) <br />
Gloin (Starting) <br />
Farin x2 <br />
Fror x2 <br />
<br />
Posesiones  (13 cards)<br />
<br />
Axe of Erebor x1 <br />
Gimlis battle axe, Trusted weapon x1 <br />
Dwarven axe x3 <br />
Hand axe x4 <br />
Dwarven braces x4 <br />
<br />
Tales  (4 cards)<br />
Greatest kingdom of my people x1 <br />
Here is a good rock x1 <br />
Song of Durin x1 (Against Moria, Your toughest match-up) <br />
Ever my heart rises x1 <br />
<br />
Robar (12 cards)<br />
<br />
Delving x4 <br />
Calculated risk x4 <br />
Search far and wide x4 <br />
<br />
Bonus  (15 cards)<br />
<br />
Flurry of blows x4 <br />
Axe strike x4 <br />
Cleaving blow x4 <br />
Stout and strong x1 <br />
Battle fury x2<br />
<br />
Total: 50 cards<br />
<br />
I know this deck is Grimable, but, it´s a risk you must take in this kind of deck. I don´t write the shadow side, but i suppose the better choice is clasic moria swarms.<br />
Basically, you have weapons, draw events and pumpers. At the beggining, you shouldn´t give many twilight, until you get one of the companions. Almost cards cost 0 o 1 twilight, so, you can fight against few minions. <br />
<br />
     -->Stack: This deck use the stacking card of the dwarf to get advantage in the battlefield. The deck abuse the cards like EVER MY HEART RISE, HERE IS A GOOD ROCK, COURTESY OF MY HALL... A sample deck would be as the following:<br />
<br />
Frodo <br />
Ring <br />
<br />
Tales (7 cards)<br />
<br />
3 x Ever my heart rises <br />
2 x Here is a good rock <br />
2 x Greatest Kingdom of my people <br />
<br />
Companion (6 cards)<br />
<br />
1 x Gimli FA (Starting)<br />
1 x Gloin (Starting)<br />
2 x Farin <br />
2 x Fror<br />
<br />
Possesions (8 cards)<br />
<br />
1 x Gimli´s helm<br />
2 x Axe of Erebor<br />
3 x Dwarven axe<br />
2 x Hand axe <br />
<br />
Condition (6 cards)<br />
<br />
3 x Endurance of Dwarves<br />
2 x Dwarven heart<br />
1 x Preparation<br />
<br />
Events  (17 cards)<br />
<br />
4 x Defending the keep <br />
4 x Battle Tested<br />
2 x Slaked Thirst<br />
2 x Toss me<br />
1 x Disquiet of our people<br />
1 x Restless Axe (to cycle EmHR)<br />
3 x Dwarven foresight (to take what you need, and combo with COURTESY OF MY HALL)<br />
<br />
<br />
Total: 44 cards<br />
<br />
With the new Gimli, this deck is posible. Before, you dead to Sarumna´s power or something to destroy condition. And, with the new site 1 (Dunharrow plateau), you can play one of your condition, EmHR principally. DWARVEN FORESIGHT allow you take any card of your condition. With PREPARATION, you may take any free people card of the discard pile. BATTLE TESTED is always a +4 pump, and slaked thirst make GRIMA, WORMTONGE useless. DWARVEN HEART is for healing, and +1 to Gimli with AXE OF EREBOR. DEFENDING THE KEEP recycling the conditions. Same with RESTLESS AXE.<br />
<br />
<br />
    -->Preparing for shadow: I never use this deck, so i don´t put the sample deck. It´s based in draw, with events like DELVING, MITHRIL SHAFT... You can use any shadow with this deck, but you must try don´t clog yourself.<br />
<br />
    <br />
    -->Discard: This deck is based in throw to waste many shadow resource. To this task, you use events like NOBODY TOSSES A DWARF, GREATEST KINGDOM OF MY PEOPLE and cards of elf culture, like WHITE ARROWS OF LORIEN. I don´t use this deck either, but a sample decklist is:<br />
<br />
Frodo<br />
Ring<br />
<br />
Companions  (8 cards)<br />
<br />
Gimli, son of Gloin (starting)<br />
Legolas, archer of Mirkwood (starting)<br />
Fror, Gimli´s kinsman  x1<br />
Farin, dwarven emissary  x1<br />
Gloin x1<br />
Lorien swordman x3<br />
<br />
Allies  (1 cards)<br />
<br />
Grimir, dwarven elder x1<br />
<br />
<br />
Weapons (11 cards)<br />
<br />
Elven bow x3<br />
Dwarven axe x4<br />
Hand axe  x4<br />
<br />
Condition (6 cards)<br />
<br />
Grestest kingdom of my people x1<br />
White arrows of Lorien  x3<br />
Far seeing eyes x2<br />
<br />
<br />
Events (10 cards)<br />
<br />
Nobody tosses a dwarf x4<br />
Storm of argument x2<br />
Flurry of blows  x4<br />
<br />
Total: 36 cards<br />
<br />
I don´t know if this deck runs well. I play LORIEN SWORDMAN because they rock with archery. And i play LEGOLAS, ARCHER OF MIRKWOOD to have some healing. GRIMIR allows recycle your NOBODY TOSSES A DWARF. I don´t play GIMLI´S BATTLE AXE, because DWARVEN AXE is better in this deck. WHITE ARROWS OF LORIEN an FAR SEEING EYES discard some cards of opponent hand. GREAT KINGDOM OF MY PEOPLE is great against any deck with orcs. STORM OF ARGUMENT has the same function than GRIMIR, and FLURRY OF BLOWS wins skirmish for itself.<br />
Shadow side must be the same strategy. Sauron, with DESPERATE DEFENSE OF THE RING and TOWER OF BARAD DUR may can work well.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Well, this is the end. I hope you enjoy with this and, once more, sorry for my English if i made some mistake with grammar o spelling. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=5279&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
